@maeipaint knows alll the tricks for creating crimped waves, perfect for summer. ☀️ Here's how she does it: 

#PROtechnique:
"✖️First: EIMI Body Crafter. A flexible volumizing spray to prep my hair before the blow dry. Lightweight but gives my hair enough body to use as a base! Don’t skip the prep steps.
✖️Next: EIMI Dry Me Dry Shampoo. This is a must-have for every day oil absorption without feeling like there’s too much build up in the hair.
✖️Last: EIMI Sugar Lift. Instead of a salt spray, a sugar spray! For added volume and grit. Can be used on wet or dry hair. In this case I utilized it as my last step in adding texture and volume to piece out the waves a bit more. Spray, scrunch and manipulate to your liking."

#wellahair #wellalife #wellaeducation #stylistspotlight @wellahairusa

Can we get a 👏 for the texture and movement @marialantoshair created with this bob?! Here's how she did it: 

#PROtechnique:
"*Starting at the nape, I used a closed blade method. The less you move the blade up and down, and the closer the blade is to the hair, the heavier and less textured your ends will be.
*I increased movement of the blade (more open) the higher up the head I went to create volume and softness.
*The vertical sections add some layers and frame for emphasis around the face."

#PROtools: 
"-Wella Oil Reflections Luminous Smoothing Oil applied on damp, towel-dried hair to give a shiny natural luster to the blow out styling
-Wella EIMI Thermal Image for heat protection before hot tool
-Wella EIMI Ocean Spritz as a finishing product for a super beachy texture"
